This command retrieves and displays the status information of an environment.

Usage: ddeploy status

The script displays the following information:

- HTTP Status: The HTTP status of the environment.
- Docker Status: The status of the Docker containers.
- Last build: The timestamp of the last build.
- Branch: The branch associated with the environment.
- Commit: The commit information associated with the environment.

Services:
The script also displays the status of the Docker services running within the environment, including the name, image, and status of each service.

